comment: I get your point about saying that JD shouldn't have lost his role(s) for being an abuser, therefore AH shouldn't lose her role(s) for being an abuser. However, I can't agree with you as the context of the situations are completely different. JD was accused by his ex-wife 2years(!!!) after their divorce of abusing her throughout their entire relationship. While he did label her a liar by denying that he ever physically abused her, he lost major roles, his reputation in the business, and basically ruined his life - but he did not accuse her of abusing him, although she did. I can understand why, almost any man would find that too embarrassing to admit, they would see it as emasculating. They shouldn't, but most men would. But again, he did not go on the offensive by accusing her of a very real thing. On the other hand, in the case of AH, she waited 2 years to accuse him falsely and try to destroy him. It would be bad enough were she only a vicious liar and it had come out that she had, in fact lied, and JD never abused her. But she didn't just lie, she was nasty and vindictive when SHE was actually the abuser and in so MANY ways, too. It's beyond sickening. So, no, the situations are not the same. If a man  loses his career because he is found and proven to be an abuser, likewise, a woman who is found and proven to be an abuser should also lose her career. Or the reverse if a man is found and proven to be an abuser and does not lose his career, then a woman found and proven to be an abuser should also not lose her career - as you stated. But JD was accused of being an abuser and found to be so, without any proof and lost his career, etc. AH has been proven to be a liar, falsely accusing JD and proven to be the abuser - he didn't accuse her of it and I think we can be assured of the fact that he never would have, either. So yes, she absolutely should lose her career over it. Maybe that might be enough for her to seek the psychiatric help she needs for her mental illness. But as she is also very obviously at the very least a narcissistic personality, who can never accept responsibility for her actions, in fact always sees and portrays herself as the victim, that 'I need psychiatric help' moment will never occur, no matter what consequences she faces for her actions. I was never a huge fan of JD, while I can do nothing but admit that he is extremely talented, many of his roles and in many of his interviews, I found him a little too offbeat, weird, or just not artistically to my tastes. But I have seen enough and very varied work of his to honestly say that he is a really talented actor. I haven't seen any of AH's work, that I am aware of, so couldn't comment on her abilities one way or the other. Based on the video of her testimony when she was being deposed, though, I would have to think not. I myself suffered emotional and verbal abuse in my marriage and I have known people who have been physically abused in theirs and also studied psychology in college. She did not behave like an abused woman in any way. She was rude and condescending to the attorney taking her deposition. She was aggressive and rude with police in a video shown. She hit JD on video, even in what could be perceived as a joking way in the video. Showed an aggressive and possessive attitude towards JD in red carpet videos and also physically aggressive behavior towards other men (co-workers), her father, and other partners in interviews and other videos that are totally inconsistent, the complete opposite type of behavior you would see from a woman who was or is being physically abused by her spouse. So I never believed her claims, but I hadn't thought that she was abusing JD until I heard the audio tapes of her  screaming at him and berating him, admitting to hitting him and calling him a coward and a baby for walking out and "running away" after she physically assaulted him or started arguments with him. Not surprised, in hindsight, based on said interviews and her behavior seen in videos, but I hadn't suspected it prior to the audio tapes that proved it and all that has come out since. So I just can't agree with your stance, even though you are certainly entitled to your opinion.

I agree with the opening comments but have caveats. If you believe a possible victim of DV should not be terminated then you should believe that a possible perpetrator of DV should not be terminated. Not quite the same thing as  if you believe a proven victim of DV should not be terminated then you should believe that a proven perpetrator of DV should not be terminated. I believe the former, I do not believe the latter. 

However, you then have to get in to a discussion of what constitutes proof. Losing or winning a civil court case? Well, that has proven to be a bit of an unreliable yard stick when the judge is fucking corrupt. Criminal conviction? Very high bar to jump over. How about being utterly destroyed in the court of public opinion? Tricky territory.

Listen, I also hate AH with a passion for this whole bullshit. But I'm not gonna give my hopes up for this new report mainly cause pretty much the exact same rumor came out months ago. So honestly, if this ends up false, I wouldn't be very disappointed. 
However, if this does end up true, I wouldn't be very shocked either. It seems that one of the narratives that the media wants to push is that JD and AH were both equally abusive to each other (which we know isn't the case). To me, it seems like because of all the bad PR Warner Bros received from firing JD, Warner Bros wants to go from the narrative that JD is the sole abuser to that both were equally abusive. So if this report is true, and Emilia Clarke does replace AH, then WB will see it as an accomplishment, as they'll see it as the controversy not being their problem anymore. Only problem for them with this plan, is that the public knows the truth. JD may have been on a lot of drugs, but he never actually absued AH. She actually abused him, verbally,physically, and mentally. So this "equally abusive" narrative isn't gonna work with us. So the general public is still gonna be happy that AH is gone, but also still gonna be pissed that JD is still gone aswell. So the Bad PR is still kinda there (if this report is true, that is).
